<div id="p699" class="blockpost roweven">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#8&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=699#p699">2009-10-19 04:43:55</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=90590">fuzzel</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Member</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: BEP 31 Tracker Failure Retry Extension</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>&gt; That would make all of the traffic go away.<br /><br />How exactly would what make the 'traffic go away'?<br /><br />*.sixxs.org is a full wildcard domain, can't just add random records there, how would we know which ones should be there? It is not only the various TPB trackers that are being requested. That is a similar exercise as actually having to add something to a server just because some clients are unable to do proper HTTP.<br /><br />Also, the whole point is that if somebody points a popular torrent to <a href="http://www.bittorrent.org" rel="nofollow">www.bittorrent.org</a> that you cannot just drop that hostname, unless you want to admit defeat in the DDoS that is.</p>
				</div>
