			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: BEP 31 Tracker Failure Retry Extension</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>why would you want to match ALL bittorrent trackers? I thought that this was about traffic, obviously you'd only have to match those that cause a disproportional amount of traffic, which should be a quite small amount, no?<br /><br />Not to mention that you're more or less providing an open proxy...<br /><br /><br />I'm not really convinced that this is actually a common scenario.<br /><br /><br /><br />Not to mention that - as i have stated earlier - that redirecting to the correct URL would be a much cleaner choice as your website is clearly meant to act as a proxy, redirecting to an un-proxied URL wouldn't deprive torrents of their trackers, simply telling them to never come back again on the other hand would.<br />So if anything redirects should be used (and fixed if they don't work) instead of a flat out denial of service.</p>
				</div>
