					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: BEP 31 Tracker Failure Retry Extension</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>&gt; How about documenting the already deployed &quot;min interval&quot; response,<br />&gt; and define that to be the retry interval for failures? This is already<br />&gt; implemented by uTorrent. This seems like a simpler and shorter path to<br />&gt; what you want to achieve with this proposal.<br /><br />If that retry interval can be set to 'unlimited' then that would be a partial plan. It might be 'nice' though for the user if the user can see a message from the server (which might be a real tracker) why that decision is being made for him/her/it though. As such one eventually comes into the BEP-31 proposal.</p>
				</div>
