<div id="p909" class="blockpost roweven">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#18&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=909#p909">2010-01-14 10:23:27</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=89602">arvid</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Administrator</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: BEP 31 Tracker Failure Retry Extension</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>The main problem there is that trackers can rarely be trusted to return accurate status codes. Some trackers even return html on certain errors (esp. the ones running under apache). I believe that a significant portion of trackers returning error codes are not permanent errors, and should be retried, maybe even the majority.<br /><br />&quot;min interval&quot; is already a de-facto standard and supported by the majority of peers. Documenting it must surely be the shortest path to achieving fuzzel's goals.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
